  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study focuses on trefoil family factor (TFF) peptides in sputum in lung diseases. The
      investigators hypothesize that TFF peptides are upregulated in lung diseases characterized by
      mucus hypersecretion.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
